{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"A year ago, I spoke to you about a book"},{"time":4000,"text":"that I was just in the process of completing,"},{"time":7000,"text":"that has come out in the interim, and I would like to talk to you today"},{"time":10000,"text":"about some of the controversies that that book inspired."},{"time":14000,"text":"The book is called \"The Blank Slate,\""},{"time":16000,"text":"based on the popular idea"},{"time":18000,"text":"that the human mind is a blank slate,"},{"time":20000,"text":"and that all of its structure comes from"},{"time":23000,"text":"socialization, culture, parenting, experience."},{"time":27000,"text":"The \"blank slate\" was an influential idea in the 20th century."},{"time":31000,"text":"Here are a few quotes indicating that:"},{"time":34000,"text":"\"Man has no nature,\" from the historian"},{"time":36000,"text":"Jose Ortega y Gasset;"},{"time":38000,"text":"\"Man has no instincts,\" from the"},{"time":40000,"text":"anthropologist Ashley Montagu;"},{"time":42000,"text":"\"The human brain is capable of a full range of behaviors"},{"time":45000,"text":"and predisposed to none,\" from the late scientist Stephen Jay Gould."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50000,"text":"There are a number of reasons to doubt that the human mind"},{"time":52000,"text":"is a blank slate,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and some of them just come from common sense."},{"time":56000,"text":"As many people have told me over the years,"},{"time":59000,"text":"anyone who's had more than one child"},{"time":61000,"text":"knows that kids come into the world"},{"time":64000,"text":"with certain temperaments and talents;"},{"time":66000,"text":"it doesn't all come from the outside."},{"time":69000,"text":"Oh, and anyone who"},{"time":71000,"text":"has both a child and a house pet"},{"time":74000,"text":"has surely noticed that the child, exposed to speech,"},{"time":76000,"text":"will acquire a human language,"},{"time":78000,"text":"whereas the house pet won't,"},{"time":80000,"text":"presumably because of some innate different between them."},{"time":83000,"text":"And anyone who's ever been"},{"time":85000,"text":"in a heterosexual relationship knows that"},{"time":87000,"text":"the minds of men and the minds of women are not indistinguishable."},{"time":91000,"text":"There are also, I think,"},{"time":93000,"text":"increasing results from"},{"time":95000,"text":"the scientific study of humans"},{"time":97000,"text":"that, indeed, we're not born blank slates."},{"time":100000,"text":"One of them, from anthropology,"},{"time":103000,"text":"is the study of human universals."},{"time":105000,"text":"If you've ever taken anthropology, you know that it's a --"},{"time":107000,"text":"kind of an occupational"},{"time":109000,"text":"pleasure of anthropologists to show"},{"time":111000,"text":"how exotic other cultures can be,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and that there are places out there where, supposedly,"},{"time":116000,"text":"everything is the opposite to the way it is here."},{"time":119000,"text":"But if you instead"},{"time":121000,"text":"look at what is common to the world's cultures,"},{"time":125000,"text":"you find that there is an enormously rich set"},{"time":127000,"text":"of behaviors and emotions"},{"time":130000,"text":"and ways of construing the world"},{"time":132000,"text":"that can be found in all of the world's 6,000-odd cultures."},{"time":136000,"text":"The anthropologist Donald Brown has tried to list them all,"},{"time":139000,"text":"and they range from aesthetics,"},{"time":141000,"text":"affection and age statuses"},{"time":144000,"text":"all the way down to weaning, weapons, weather,"},{"time":147000,"text":"attempts to control, the color white"},{"time":149000,"text":"and a worldview."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"Also, genetics and neuroscience"},{"time":153000,"text":"are increasingly showing that the brain"},{"time":155000,"text":"is intricately structured."},{"time":158000,"text":"This is a recent study by the neurobiologist Paul Thompson"},{"time":160000,"text":"and his colleagues in which they --"},{"time":162000,"text":"using MRI --"},{"time":164000,"text":"measured the distribution of gray matter --"},{"time":167000,"text":"that is, the outer layer of the cortex --"},{"time":170000,"text":"in a large sample of pairs of people."},{"time":173000,"text":"They coded correlations in the thickness"},{"time":177000,"text":"of gray matter in different parts of the brain"},{"time":179000,"text":"using a false color scheme, in which"},{"time":182000,"text":"no difference is coded as purple,"},{"time":185000,"text":"and any color other than purple indicates"},{"time":187000,"text":"a statistically significant correlation."},{"time":189000,"text":"Well, this is what happens when you pair people up at random."},{"time":192000,"text":"By definition, two people picked at random"},{"time":195000,"text":"can't have correlations in the distribution"},{"time":197000,"text":"of gray matter in the cortex."},{"time":200000,"text":"This is what happens in people who share"},{"time":203000,"text":"half of their DNA -- fraternal twins."},{"time":206000,"text":"And as you can see, large amounts of the brain"},{"time":208000,"text":"are not purple, showing that if one person"},{"time":211000,"text":"has a thicker bit of cortex"},{"time":214000,"text":"in that region, so does his fraternal twin."},{"time":217000,"text":"And here's what happens if you"},{"time":221000,"text":"get a pair of people who share all their DNA --"},{"time":223000,"text":"namely, clones or identical twins."},{"time":226000,"text":"And you can see huge areas of cortex where there are"},{"time":230000,"text":"massive correlations in the distribution of gray matter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"Now, these aren't just"},{"time":235000,"text":"differences in anatomy,"},{"time":237000,"text":"like the shape of your ear lobes,"},{"time":239000,"text":"but they have consequences in thought and behavior"},{"time":243000,"text":"that are well illustrated in this famous cartoon by Charles Addams:"},{"time":247000,"text":"\"Separated at birth, the Mallifert twins meet accidentally.\""},{"time":252000,"text":"As you can see, there are two inventors"},{"time":254000,"text":"with identical contraptions in their lap, meeting"},{"time":256000,"text":"in the waiting room of a patent attorney."},{"time":258000,"text":"Now, the cartoon is not such an exaggeration, because"},{"time":261000,"text":"studies of identical twins who were separated at birth"},{"time":264000,"text":"and then tested in adulthood"},{"time":266000,"text":"show that they have astonishing similarities."},{"time":269000,"text":"And this happens in every pair of identical twins"},{"time":272000,"text":"separated at birth ever studied --"},{"time":274000,"text":"but much less so with fraternal twins separated at birth."},{"time":277000,"text":"My favorite example is a pair of twins,"},{"time":280000,"text":"one of whom was brought up"},{"time":282000,"text":"as a Catholic in a Nazi family in Germany,"},{"time":286000,"text":"the other brought up in a Jewish family in Trinidad."},{"time":290000,"text":"When they walked into the lab in Minnesota,"},{"time":292000,"text":"they were wearing identical navy blue shirts with epaulettes;"},{"time":295000,"text":"both of them liked to dip buttered toast in coffee,"},{"time":298000,"text":"both of them kept rubber bands around their wrists,"},{"time":302000,"text":"both of them flushed the toilet before using it as well as after,"},{"time":305000,"text":"and both of them liked to surprise people"},{"time":308000,"text":"by sneezing in crowded elevators to watch them jump."},{"time":312000,"text":"Now --"},{"time":314000,"text":"the story might seem to good to be true,"},{"time":316000,"text":"but when you administer"},{"time":318000,"text":"batteries of psychological tests,"},{"time":321000,"text":"you get the same results -- namely,"},{"time":323000,"text":"identical twins separated at birth show"},{"time":325000,"text":"quite astonishing similarities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"Now, given both the common sense"},{"time":329000,"text":"and scientific data"},{"time":331000,"text":"calling the doctrine of the blank slate into question,"},{"time":333000,"text":"why should it have been such an appealing notion?"},{"time":336000,"text":"Well, there are a number of political reasons why people have found it congenial."},{"time":339000,"text":"The foremost is that if we're blank slates,"},{"time":342000,"text":"then, by definition, we are equal,"},{"time":344000,"text":"because zero equals zero equals zero."},{"time":347000,"text":"But if something is written on the slate,"},{"time":349000,"text":"then some people could have more of it than others,"},{"time":351000,"text":"and according to this line of thinking, that would justify"},{"time":353000,"text":"discrimination and inequality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356000,"text":"Another political fear of human nature"},{"time":359000,"text":"is that if we are blank slates,"},{"time":361000,"text":"we can perfect mankind --"},{"time":363000,"text":"the age-old dream of the perfectibility of our species"},{"time":366000,"text":"through social engineering."},{"time":368000,"text":"Whereas, if we're born with certain instincts,"},{"time":370000,"text":"then perhaps some of them might condemn us"},{"time":372000,"text":"to selfishness, prejudice and violence."},{"time":376000,"text":"Well, in the book, I argue that these are, in fact, non sequiturs."},{"time":380000,"text":"And just to make a long story short:"},{"time":382000,"text":"first of all, the concept of fairness"},{"time":384000,"text":"is not the same as the concept of sameness."},{"time":387000,"text":"And so when Thomas Jefferson wrote"},{"time":389000,"text":"in the Declaration of Independence,"},{"time":391000,"text":"\"We hold these truths to be self-evident,"},{"time":393000,"text":"that all men are created equal,\""},{"time":396000,"text":"he did not mean \"We hold these truths to be self-evident,"},{"time":398000,"text":"that all men are clones.\""},{"time":401000,"text":"Rather, that all men are equal in terms of their rights,"},{"time":404000,"text":"and that every person ought to be treated"},{"time":407000,"text":"as an individual, and not prejudged"},{"time":409000,"text":"by the statistics of particular groups"},{"time":411000,"text":"that they may belong to."},{"time":414000,"text":"Also, even if we were born"},{"time":416000,"text":"with certain ignoble motives,"},{"time":418000,"text":"they don't automatically lead to ignoble behavior."},{"time":421000,"text":"That is because the human mind"},{"time":423000,"text":"is a complex system with many parts,"},{"time":425000,"text":"and some of them can inhibit others."},{"time":428000,"text":"For example, there's excellent reason to believe"},{"time":431000,"text":"that virtually all humans are born with a moral sense,"},{"time":435000,"text":"and that we have cognitive abilities that allow us"},{"time":438000,"text":"to profit from the lessons of history."},{"time":440000,"text":"So even if people did have impulses"},{"time":442000,"text":"towards selfishness or greed,"},{"time":444000,"text":"that's not the only thing in the skull,"},{"time":446000,"text":"and there are other parts of the mind that can counteract them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"In the book, I"},{"time":451000,"text":"go over controversies such as this one,"},{"time":453000,"text":"and a number of other hot buttons,"},{"time":456000,"text":"hot zones, Chernobyls, third rails, and so on --"},{"time":459000,"text":"including the arts, cloning, crime,"},{"time":461000,"text":"free will, education, evolution,"},{"time":463000,"text":"gender differences, God, homosexuality,"},{"time":466000,"text":"infanticide, inequality, Marxism, morality,"},{"time":468000,"text":"Nazism, parenting, politics,"},{"time":470000,"text":"race, rape, religion, resource depletion,"},{"time":472000,"text":"social engineering, technological risk and war."},{"time":475000,"text":"And needless to say, there were certain risks"},{"time":477000,"text":"in taking on these subjects."},{"time":481000,"text":"When I wrote a first draft of the book,"},{"time":484000,"text":"I circulated it to a number of colleagues for comments,"},{"time":486000,"text":"and here are some of"},{"time":489000,"text":"the reactions that I got:"},{"time":491000,"text":"\"Better get a security camera for your house.\""},{"time":495000,"text":"\"Don't expect to get any more awards, job offers"},{"time":498000,"text":"or positions in scholarly societies.\""},{"time":501000,"text":"\"Tell your publisher not to list your hometown"},{"time":503000,"text":"in your author bio.\""},{"time":506000,"text":"\"Do you have tenure?\""},{"time":508000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510000,"text":"Well, the book came out in October,"},{"time":512000,"text":"and nothing terrible has happened."},{"time":517000,"text":"I -- I like --"},{"time":520000,"text":"There was indeed reason to be nervous,"},{"time":522000,"text":"and there were moments in which I did feel nervous,"},{"time":524000,"text":"knowing the history"},{"time":526000,"text":"of what has happened to people"},{"time":528000,"text":"who've taken controversial stands"},{"time":530000,"text":"or discovered disquieting findings"},{"time":533000,"text":"in the behavioral sciences."},{"time":535000,"text":"There are many cases, some of which I talk about in the book,"},{"time":538000,"text":"of people who have been slandered, called Nazis,"},{"time":542000,"text":"physically assaulted, threatened with criminal prosecution"},{"time":545000,"text":"for stumbling across or arguing"},{"time":549000,"text":"about controversial findings."},{"time":552000,"text":"And you never know when you're going to"},{"time":554000,"text":"come across one of these booby traps."},{"time":556000,"text":"My favorite example is a pair of psychologists"},{"time":558000,"text":"who did research on left-handers,"},{"time":561000,"text":"and published some data showing that left-handers are, on average,"},{"time":564000,"text":"more susceptible to disease, more prone to accidents"},{"time":567000,"text":"and have a shorter lifespan."},{"time":569000,"text":"It's not clear, by the way, since then,"},{"time":571000,"text":"whether that is an accurate generalization,"},{"time":574000,"text":"but the data at the time seemed to support that."},{"time":577000,"text":"Well, pretty soon they were barraged"},{"time":579000,"text":"with enraged letters,"},{"time":582000,"text":"death threats,"},{"time":584000,"text":"ban on the topic in a number of scientific journals,"},{"time":587000,"text":"coming from irate left-handers"},{"time":590000,"text":"and their advocates,"},{"time":592000,"text":"and they were literally afraid to open their mail"},{"time":595000,"text":"because of the venom and vituperation"},{"time":598000,"text":"that they had inadvertently inspired."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"Well,"},{"time":603000,"text":"the night is young, but the book has been out"},{"time":605000,"text":"for half a year,"},{"time":607000,"text":"and nothing terrible has happened."},{"time":609000,"text":"None of the dire professional consequences"},{"time":611000,"text":"has taken place --"},{"time":613000,"text":"I haven't been"},{"time":615000,"text":"exiled from the city of Cambridge."},{"time":618000,"text":"But what I wanted to talk about"},{"time":620000,"text":"are two of these hot buttons"},{"time":623000,"text":"that have aroused the strongest response"},{"time":627000,"text":"in the 80-odd reviews"},{"time":629000,"text":"that The Blank Slate has received."},{"time":632000,"text":"I'll just put that list up for a few seconds,"},{"time":635000,"text":"and see if you can guess which two"},{"time":637000,"text":"-- I would estimate that probably two of these topics"},{"time":639000,"text":"inspired probably 90 percent"},{"time":642000,"text":"of the reaction in the various reviews"},{"time":645000,"text":"and radio interviews."},{"time":647000,"text":"It's not violence and war,"},{"time":649000,"text":"it's not race, it's not gender,"},{"time":651000,"text":"it's not Marxism, it's not Nazism."},{"time":654000,"text":"They are: the arts and parenting."},{"time":657000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":659000,"text":"So let me tell you what"},{"time":661000,"text":"aroused such irate responses,"},{"time":663000,"text":"and I'll let you decide if whether they --"},{"time":666000,"text":"the claims are really that outrageous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668000,"text":"Let me start with the arts."},{"time":671000,"text":"I note that among the long list of human universals"},{"time":673000,"text":"that I presented a few slides ago"},{"time":676000,"text":"are art."},{"time":678000,"text":"There is no society ever discovered"},{"time":681000,"text":"in the remotest corner of the world that has not had something"},{"time":684000,"text":"that we would consider the arts."},{"time":688000,"text":"Visual arts -- decoration of surfaces and bodies --"},{"time":690000,"text":"appears to be a human universal."},{"time":692000,"text":"The telling of stories, music,"},{"time":694000,"text":"dance, poetry -- found in all cultures,"},{"time":697000,"text":"and many of the motifs and themes"},{"time":700000,"text":"that"},{"time":703000,"text":"give us pleasure in the arts"},{"time":705000,"text":"can be found in all human societies:"},{"time":709000,"text":"a preference for symmetrical forms,"},{"time":712000,"text":"the use of repetition and variation,"},{"time":714000,"text":"even things as specific as the fact"},{"time":716000,"text":"that in poetry all over the world,"},{"time":718000,"text":"you have lines that are very close"},{"time":721000,"text":"to three seconds long, separated by pauses."},{"time":724000,"text":"Now, on the other hand,"},{"time":726000,"text":"in the second half of the 20th century,"},{"time":728000,"text":"the arts are frequently said to be in decline."},{"time":731000,"text":"And I have a collection,"},{"time":733000,"text":"probably 10 or 15 headlines, from highbrow magazines"},{"time":736000,"text":"deploring the fact that"},{"time":738000,"text":"the arts are in decline in our time."},{"time":741000,"text":"I'll give you a couple of representative quotes:"},{"time":744000,"text":"\"We can assert with some confidence that our own period is"},{"time":746000,"text":"one of decline, that the standards of culture are lower"},{"time":749000,"text":"than they were 50 years ago, and that the evidences of this decline"},{"time":752000,"text":"are visible in every department of human activity.\""},{"time":755000,"text":"That's a quote from T. S. Eliot, a little more than 50 years ago."},{"time":758000,"text":"And a more recent one:"},{"time":760000,"text":"\"The possibility of sustaining high culture in our time"},{"time":762000,"text":"is becoming increasing problematical."},{"time":765000,"text":"Serious book stores are losing their franchise,"},{"time":767000,"text":"nonprofit theaters are surviving primarily"},{"time":769000,"text":"by commercializing their repertory,"},{"time":771000,"text":"symphony orchestras are diluting their programs,"},{"time":773000,"text":"public television is increasing its dependence"},{"time":775000,"text":"on reruns of British sitcoms,"},{"time":778000,"text":"classical radio stations are dwindling,"},{"time":780000,"text":"museums are resorting to blockbuster shows, dance is dying.\""},{"time":782000,"text":"That's from Robert Brustein,"},{"time":784000,"text":"the famous drama critic and director,"},{"time":787000,"text":"in The New Republic about five years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790000,"text":"Well, in fact, the arts are not in decline."},{"time":793000,"text":"I don't think this will as a surprise to anyone in this room,"},{"time":796000,"text":"but by any standard"},{"time":798000,"text":"they have never been flourishing"},{"time":800000,"text":"to a greater extent."},{"time":802000,"text":"There are, of course, entirely new art forms"},{"time":805000,"text":"and new media, many of which you've heard"},{"time":807000,"text":"over these few days."},{"time":810000,"text":"By any economic standard,"},{"time":812000,"text":"the demand for art of all forms"},{"time":815000,"text":"is skyrocketing,"},{"time":817000,"text":"as you can tell from the price of opera tickets,"},{"time":819000,"text":"by the number of books sold,"},{"time":821000,"text":"by the number of books published,"},{"time":823000,"text":"the number of musical titles released,"},{"time":826000,"text":"the number of new albums and so on."},{"time":829000,"text":"The only grain of truth to this"},{"time":831000,"text":"complaint that the arts are in decline"},{"time":833000,"text":"come from three spheres."},{"time":837000,"text":"One of them is in elite art since the 1930s --"},{"time":840000,"text":"say, the kinds of works performed"},{"time":842000,"text":"by major symphony orchestras,"},{"time":844000,"text":"where most of the repertory is before 1930,"},{"time":848000,"text":"or the works shown in"},{"time":850000,"text":"major galleries and prestigious museums."},{"time":854000,"text":"In literary criticism and analysis,"},{"time":856000,"text":"probably 40 or 50 years ago,"},{"time":858000,"text":"literary critics were a kind of cultural hero;"},{"time":861000,"text":"now they're kind of a national joke."},{"time":863000,"text":"And the humanities and arts programs"},{"time":866000,"text":"in the universities, which by many measures,"},{"time":868000,"text":"indeed are in decline."},{"time":870000,"text":"Students are staying away in droves,"},{"time":872000,"text":"universities are disinvesting"},{"time":874000,"text":"in the arts and humanities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876000,"text":"Well, here's a diagnosis."},{"time":879000,"text":"They didn't ask me, but by their own admission,"},{"time":881000,"text":"they need all the help that they can get."},{"time":884000,"text":"And I would like to suggest that it's not a coincidence"},{"time":886000,"text":"that this supposed decline"},{"time":888000,"text":"in the elite arts and criticism"},{"time":891000,"text":"occurred in the same point in history in which"},{"time":893000,"text":"there was a widespread denial of human nature."},{"time":896000,"text":"A famous quotation can be found --"},{"time":898000,"text":"if you look on the web, you can find it in"},{"time":900000,"text":"literally scores"},{"time":902000,"text":"of English core syllabuses --"},{"time":905000,"text":"\"In or about December 1910,"},{"time":908000,"text":"human nature changed.\""},{"time":910000,"text":"A paraphrase of a quote by Virginia Woolf,"},{"time":913000,"text":"and there's some debate"},{"time":915000,"text":"as to what she actually meant by that."},{"time":917000,"text":"But it's very clear, looking at these syllabuses,"},{"time":919000,"text":"that -- it's used now"},{"time":921000,"text":"as a way of saying that all forms"},{"time":925000,"text":"of appreciation of art"},{"time":927000,"text":"that were in place for centuries, or millennia,"},{"time":931000,"text":"in the 20th century were discarded."},{"time":934000,"text":"The beauty and pleasure in art --"},{"time":936000,"text":"probably a human universal --"},{"time":938000,"text":"were -- began to be considered saccharine,"},{"time":940000,"text":"or kitsch, or commercial."},{"time":943000,"text":"Barnett Newman had a famous quote that \"the impulse of modern art"},{"time":946000,"text":"is the desire to destroy beauty\" --"},{"time":949000,"text":"which was considered bourgeois or tacky."},{"time":952000,"text":"And here's just one example."},{"time":954000,"text":"I mean, this is perhaps a representative example"},{"time":957000,"text":"of the visual depiction of the female form"},{"time":960000,"text":"in the 15th century;"},{"time":962000,"text":"here is a representative example"},{"time":964000,"text":"of the depiction of the female form in the 20th century."},{"time":968000,"text":"And, as you can see, there -- something has changed"},{"time":970000,"text":"in the way the elite arts"},{"time":972000,"text":"appeal to the senses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974000,"text":"Indeed, in movements of modernism"},{"time":976000,"text":"and post-modernism,"},{"time":978000,"text":"there was visual art without beauty,"},{"time":980000,"text":"literature without narrative and plot,"},{"time":982000,"text":"poetry without meter and rhyme,"},{"time":984000,"text":"architecture and planning without ornament,"},{"time":986000,"text":"human scale, green space and natural light,"},{"time":989000,"text":"music without melody and rhythm,"},{"time":991000,"text":"and criticism without clarity,"},{"time":993000,"text":"attention to aesthetics and insight into the human condition."},{"time":996000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":998000,"text":"Let me give just you an example to back up that last statement."},{"time":1001000,"text":"But here, there -- one of the most famous literary"},{"time":1003000,"text":"English scholars of our time"},{"time":1005000,"text":"is the Berkeley professor,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"Judith Butler."},{"time":1009000,"text":"And here is an example of"},{"time":1011000,"text":"one of her analyses:"},{"time":1014000,"text":"\"The move from a structuralist account in which capital"},{"time":1016000,"text":"is understood to structure social relations"},{"time":1018000,"text":"in relatively homologous ways"},{"time":1020000,"text":"to a view of hegemony in which power relations are subject to repetition,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"convergence and rearticulation"},{"time":1025000,"text":"brought the question of temporality into the thinking of structure,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"and marked a shift from the form of Althusserian theory"},{"time":1030000,"text":"that takes structural totalities as theoretical objects ...\""},{"time":1033000,"text":"Well, you get the idea."},{"time":1036000,"text":"By the way, this is one sentence --"},{"time":1038000,"text":"you can actually parse it."},{"time":1042000,"text":"Well, the argument in \"The Blank Slate\""},{"time":1044000,"text":"was that elite art and criticism"},{"time":1046000,"text":"in the 20th century,"},{"time":1048000,"text":"although not the arts in general,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"have disdained beauty, pleasure,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"clarity, insight and style."},{"time":1055000,"text":"People are staying away from elite art and criticism."},{"time":1059000,"text":"What a puzzle -- I wonder why."},{"time":1062000,"text":"Well, this turned out to be probably"},{"time":1064000,"text":"the most controversial claim in the book."},{"time":1066000,"text":"Someone asked me whether I stuck it in"},{"time":1068000,"text":"in order to deflect ire"},{"time":1071000,"text":"from discussions of gender and Nazism"},{"time":1074000,"text":"and race and so on. I won't comment on that."},{"time":1078000,"text":"But it certainly inspired"},{"time":1081000,"text":"an energetic reaction"},{"time":1084000,"text":"from many university professors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1087000,"text":"Well, the other hot button is parenting."},{"time":1090000,"text":"And the starting point is the -- for that discussion"},{"time":1093000,"text":"was the fact that we have all"},{"time":1095000,"text":"been subject to the advice"},{"time":1097000,"text":"of the parenting industrial complex."},{"time":1100000,"text":"Now, here is -- here is a"},{"time":1102000,"text":"representative quote from a besieged mother:"},{"time":1105000,"text":"\"I'm overwhelmed with parenting advice."},{"time":1107000,"text":"I'm supposed to do lots of physical activity with my kids"},{"time":1109000,"text":"so I can instill in them a physical fitness habit"},{"time":1112000,"text":"so they'll grow up to be healthy adults."},{"time":1114000,"text":"And I'm supposed to do all kinds of intellectual play"},{"time":1116000,"text":"so they'll grow up smart."},{"time":1118000,"text":"And there are all kinds of play -- clay for finger dexterity,"},{"time":1121000,"text":"word games for reading success, large motor play,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"small motor play. I feel like I could devote my life"},{"time":1126000,"text":"to figuring out what to play with my kids.\""},{"time":1129000,"text":"I think anyone who's recently been a parent can sympathize"},{"time":1131000,"text":"with this mother."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134000,"text":"Well, here's some sobering facts about parenting."},{"time":1137000,"text":"Most studies of parenting on which this advice is based"},{"time":1141000,"text":"are useless. They're useless because they don't control"},{"time":1144000,"text":"for heritability. They measure some correlation"},{"time":1147000,"text":"between what the parents do, how the children turn out"},{"time":1150000,"text":"and assume a causal relation:"},{"time":1152000,"text":"that the parenting shaped the child."},{"time":1154000,"text":"Parents who talk a lot to their kids"},{"time":1156000,"text":"have kids who grow up to be articulate,"},{"time":1158000,"text":"parents who spank their kids have kids who grow up"},{"time":1160000,"text":"to be violent and so on."},{"time":1162000,"text":"And very few of them control for the possibility"},{"time":1165000,"text":"that parents pass on genes for --"},{"time":1168000,"text":"that increase the chances a child will be articulate"},{"time":1170000,"text":"or violent and so on."},{"time":1172000,"text":"Until the studies are redone with adoptive children,"},{"time":1175000,"text":"who provide an environment"},{"time":1177000,"text":"but not genes to their kids,"},{"time":1179000,"text":"we have no way of knowing whether these conclusions are valid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1182000,"text":"The genetically controlled studies"},{"time":1184000,"text":"have some sobering results."},{"time":1186000,"text":"Remember the Mallifert twins:"},{"time":1188000,"text":"separated at birth, then they meet in the patent office --"},{"time":1191000,"text":"remarkably similar."},{"time":1193000,"text":"Well, what would have happened if the Mallifert twins had grown up together?"},{"time":1196000,"text":"You might think, well, then they'd be even more similar,"},{"time":1199000,"text":"because not only would they share their genes,"},{"time":1201000,"text":"but they would also share their environment."},{"time":1204000,"text":"That would make them super-similar, right?"},{"time":1206000,"text":"Wrong. Identical twins, or any siblings,"},{"time":1209000,"text":"who are separated at birth are no less similar"},{"time":1213000,"text":"than if they had grown up together."},{"time":1215000,"text":"Everything that happens to you in a given home"},{"time":1217000,"text":"over all of those years"},{"time":1219000,"text":"appears to leave no permanent stamp"},{"time":1221000,"text":"on your personality or intellect."},{"time":1224000,"text":"A complementary finding, from a completely different methodology,"},{"time":1227000,"text":"is that adopted siblings reared together --"},{"time":1231000,"text":"the mirror image of identical twins reared apart,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"they share their parents, their home,"},{"time":1235000,"text":"their neighborhood,"},{"time":1237000,"text":"don't share their genes -- end up not similar at all."},{"time":1240000,"text":"OK -- two different bodies of research with a similar finding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1243000,"text":"What it suggests is that children are shaped"},{"time":1245000,"text":"not by their parents over the long run,"},{"time":1248000,"text":"but in part -- only in part -- by their genes,"},{"time":1251000,"text":"in part by their culture --"},{"time":1253000,"text":"the culture of the country at large"},{"time":1255000,"text":"and the children's own culture, namely their peer group --"},{"time":1257000,"text":"as we heard from Jill Sobule earlier today,"},{"time":1260000,"text":"that's what kids care about --"},{"time":1263000,"text":"and, to a very large extent, larger than most people are prepared to acknowledge,"},{"time":1266000,"text":"by chance: chance events in the wiring of the brain in utero;"},{"time":1269000,"text":"chance events as you live your life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1273000,"text":"So let me conclude"},{"time":1275000,"text":"with just a remark"},{"time":1277000,"text":"to bring it back to the theme of choices."},{"time":1280000,"text":"I think that the sciences of human nature --"},{"time":1282000,"text":"behavioral genetics, evolutionary psychology, \n"},{"time":1285000,"text":"neuroscience, cognitive science --"},{"time":1287000,"text":"are going to, increasingly in the years to come,"},{"time":1290000,"text":"upset various dogmas,"},{"time":1293000,"text":"careers and deeply-held political belief systems."},{"time":1296000,"text":"And that presents us with a choice."},{"time":1298000,"text":"The choice is whether certain facts about humans,"},{"time":1301000,"text":"or topics, are to be considered taboos,"},{"time":1305000,"text":"forbidden knowledge, where we shouldn't go there"},{"time":1307000,"text":"because no good can come from it,"},{"time":1309000,"text":"or whether we should explore them honestly."},{"time":1312000,"text":"I have my own"},{"time":1314000,"text":"answer to that question,"},{"time":1316000,"text":"which comes from a great artist of the 19th century,"},{"time":1319000,"text":"Anton Chekhov, who said,"},{"time":1322000,"text":"\"Man will become better when you show him"},{"time":1324000,"text":"what he is like.\""},{"time":1326000,"text":"And I think that the argument"},{"time":1328000,"text":"can't be put any more eloquently than that."},{"time":1331000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1334000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}